@startuml dkey_access_to_door_fl_unlock_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title DKEY Access To DOOR_FL Unlock Signal Flow\n(DKEY + immobilizer + door command -> front-left door state)

participant "Input_Console / command source\nDoor control command" as Cmd #F4F7FB
participant "DKEY + SMK\naccess authorization context" as Auth #E8F0FE
participant "DOOR_FL\nfront-left door owner" as Door #FFF4CC
participant "Body observers /\npanel readback" as Obs #FCE8FF

== Door Inputs ==

Cmd -> Door : door command seam\n(open / close / lock intent)
Auth -> Door : frmDigitalKeyStateMsg\nVehicleAccessState / KeyPresence
Auth -> Door : frmImmobilizerStateMsg\nImmobilizerState / KeyAuthState
activate Door
Door -> Door : normalize stale command / DKEY / immo inputs
Door -> Door : accessAuthorized when drive=0\nand key/access/auth conditions are met
Door -> Door : derive DoorFlLockState / OpenState / WindowPos
note right of Door
Representative conditions
- VehicleAccessState >= 1
- KeyPresence == 1
- immobilizer/key-auth valid
- driveState == 0
end note

== Door Publish ==

Door -> Obs : frmDoorFlStateMsg
Door -> Obs : Body::windowPos readback
deactivate Door

note over Cmd, Obs
Representative runtime chain
1. Door command arrives with DKEY and immobilizer context
2. DOOR_FL validates access authorization in park/manual conditions
3. DOOR_FL derives lock/open/window state
4. Body observers and panel readback reflect the resulting door state
end note

@enduml
